F' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>9 - 10</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Location</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Caves</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Factions</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>+KingAk'Anon, +Gemchoppers, -Meldrath</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Spells Used</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Clinging Darkness, Poison Bolt, Fear, Lifespike</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Strategy</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>The area around the Mino caves is great.  A lot of fun and GREAT exp (But poor loot usually).  There are Harpies (best loot), Elementals, Lesser Ebond Drakes and Skeletons (our favorite kill) in the area.  But the most challenging game are Mino Slavers.<br><br> 

First go to the Mino caves and peek inside.  Usually there is a single spawn just at the bend.  Cast Clinging Darkness, Poison Bolt, then send in the pet (preferable to have the pet that dishes out 14 damage which is the higher level one) and then cast Fear as needed.  You can melee to protect your pet also but you can take upwards of 25 damage a hit.  Lifespike to get it back.<br><br>

There are three really big dangers.  First, sometimes you can pull more than one and this can be difficult at times.  Second, a Mino hero sometimes spawns if the spot is used too much (you instantly die and usually don't see him before he hits).  Third, if there is a Diseased Rat in the area it will jump in and REALLY mess things up.  If you can't wait for the next spawn just go inside and try your luck, but there are some really nasty stuff inside.  I usually just took out the nearby Skeletons or Harpies then rotated back for the respawn.  You can make 3 levels easily in a day of work.<br><br>

By the way Mino slavers occasionally drop Mino Horns and Mino Axes.  I haven't really sold any of these but iI believe you can sell them to other players for some serious cash.</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Author</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'><a href ='mailto:'>Unasyn</td></tr><tr></table><br><br></table></div>